# Responsive design

## Viewport targets

| Role            | Width                                                                                                           |
| --------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Support minimum | **320px** — must not break (no horizontal scroll; core actions usable)                                          |
| Design baseline | **375px** — spacing, typography, and tap targets are tuned here                                                 |
| Below 320px     | Out of scope; no need to optimize                                                                               |
| Tablet          | Use existing Tailwind **`md:` (768px)** and **`lg:` (1024px)** — do not add custom breakpoints unless necessary |

## Implementation

- Mobile-first: base styles target `< sm` (640px); use `sm:` / `md:` / `lg:` for larger screens.
- Prefer `min-w-0`, `truncate`, and `flex-wrap` so layouts survive 320px.
- Use `100svh` (not `100vh`) for full-viewport sections when mobile browser chrome matters.
- Verify at **320px** and **375px** after UI changes; spot-check **390px** on large phones.

## High-risk areas in this repo

- **Header / footer**: below `md:` — centered logo header + fixed bottom nav (Home via logo only); `≥ md` keeps horizontal header nav.
- **Footer**: tech stack icons + SNS in one row; on mobile, bottom-nav clearance uses a `bg-background` spacer below the dark footer bar (not dark `padding-bottom`).
- **History**: sticky scroll track + commit list; full-viewport height via `SECTION_VIEWPORT_HEIGHT` on the sticky panel in `src/components/history/history-timeline.tsx` — test short viewports (e.g. iPhone SE height).
- **Constituents**: full-viewport section; below `md:` subtract `--site-bottom-nav-height` + safe area via `SECTION_VIEWPORT_HEIGHT` on the `Section` in `src/app/[locale]/(home)/page.tsx` (loading placeholder in `src/components/constituents/constituents-client.tsx`); category filter is `shrink-0` at the bottom in `constituents-section.tsx` — verify anchor scroll from bottom nav at 320px/375px; tag placement tiers (`narrow` ≤375 / `mobile` ≤767 / `desktop` ≥768) in `src/components/constituents/placement.ts`, client init + tier-crossing resize via `src/hooks/use-placed-tags.ts` (instant reposition, no pop replay).

## Out of scope for responsive work

- Do not redesign desktop layouts when fixing mobile unless asked.
- Do not introduce new breakpoint tokens in Tailwind config unless the user requests it.
